  "prompt": "Where can I get an explainer video for $100?",
  "response": "There are several platforms and services where you can find affordable explainer video creation options, often around the $100 mark. Here are a few suggestions:\n\n1. **Fiverr**: This freelance platform has numerous video creators offering services at various price points, including options for $100 or less. You can browse through portfolios, read reviews, and choose a freelancer whose style aligns with your needs.\n\n2. **Upwork**: Similar to Fiverr, this platform allows you to post a job and receive proposals from freelancers. You can set your budget and find professionals who can create an explainer video within your price range.\n\n3. **Video Creation Tools**: Websites like **Animaker**, **Vyond**, or **Renderforest** offer DIY tools that let you create your explainer videos. Many of these platforms have free trials or affordable subscription plans that could allow you to produce a video for around $100.\n\n4. **Freelance Platforms**: Websites like **PeoplePerHour** or **Guru** also allow you to find freelancers for various tasks, including video creation.\n\n5. **Local Creatives**: Sometimes local colleges or universities have students studying film or video production who may be willing to take on projects for a lower cost to gain experience.\n\nWhen searching for services, it's important to carefully review the provider's previous work and their reviews to ensure you receive quality content.",
